  <div class="section">
    <h1><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> How to Make Better Results – TIMEON KAIROS Polytechnic</h1>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-book-reader"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>1. Attend All Lectures</h3>
        <p>Being present in class helps you understand the material directly from the lecturer and stay updated on assignments.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>2. Manage Your Time Wisely</h3>
        <p>Create a study schedule and stick to it. Avoid last-minute reading and make room for revisions before exams.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-laptop-code"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>3. Use Digital Tools</h3>
        <p>Take advantage of the school portal, online notes, apps, and research tools to enhance your understanding of subjects.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-user-friends"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>4. Join Study Groups</h3>
        <p>Group discussions help you learn from others, explain concepts better, and stay motivated throughout the semester.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>5. Ask Questions</h3>
        <p>Don’t stay silent when confused. Ask your lecturers or classmates until you fully understand the topic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-edit"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>6. Practice Past Questions</h3>
        <p>Studying past exams helps you understand the exam format and the most common topics your lecturers focus on.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-heartbeat"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>7. Take Care of Your Health</h3>
        <p>Eat well, sleep well, and take breaks when needed. A healthy body and mind lead to better academic performance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-certificate"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>8. Avoid Exam Malpractice</h3>
        <p>Focus on understanding and learning. Cheating can ruin your academic future. Integrity always wins.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-rocket"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>9. Set Academic Goals</h3>
        <p>Write down your goals and track your progress. Whether it’s passing all courses or making distinctions, stay focused.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <i class="fas fa-handshake"></i>
      <div class="tip-content">
        <h3>10. Build a Good Relationship with Lecturers</h3>
        <p>Respect and communication go a long way. They may guide you, mentor you, and support you when needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

